{{Infobox scientist | honorific_prefix = | name = Bobbie Berkowitz | honorific_suffix = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = <!--(filename only, i.e. without "File:" prefix)--> | image_size = | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = <!-- if different from "name" --> | birth_date = <!--{{birth date |YYYY|MM|DD}}--> | birth_place = | death_date = <!--{{death date and age |YYYY|MM|DD |YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date)--> | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!--{{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}}--> | other_names = | pronounce = | residence = [[New York City|New York]], New York USA | citizenship = American | nationality = | fields = [[Public health nursing]], [[Health policy]] | workplaces = {{unbulleted list |[[Columbia University]] |[[University of Washington]] |[[Washington State Department of Health]] }} | patrons = | education = | alma_mater = {{unbulleted list |[[Case Western Reserve University]] |[[University of Washington]] }} | thesis_title = | thesis_url = <!--(or | thesis1_url = and | thesis2_url = )--> | thesis_year = 1990 | doctoral_advisor = | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = [[Academic administration]], [[Public health]], [[Health disparity]] | influences = | influenced = | awards = {{unbulleted list |[[National Academy of Medicine|Member NAM]] |[[American Academy of Nursing|Fellow AAN]] }} | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = <!--(or | spouses = )--> | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = {{URL|http://nursing.columbia.edu/profile/bberkowitz}} | footnotes = }}
'''Bobbie Berkowitz''' is an American professor of [[nursing]] and dean [[emeritus]] of the School of Nursing at [[Columbia University]]. She is best known for her contributions improving [[public health nursing]] and [[health systems]] with a focus on [[health disparity]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nursing.columbia.edu/bobbie-berkowitz-named-school-nursings-new-dean |title=Bobbie Berkowitz Named School of Nursing's New Dean |last= |first= |publisher=Columbia University |date=2010 |website=Columbia University |access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.chronicle.com/interactives/ivydiversity |title=The Look of Leadership in the Ivy League |last=Myers |first=Justin |publisher=The Chronicle of Higher Education |date=2013-06-09 |website=The Chronicle of Higher Education |access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://son.rochester.edu/newsroom/2017/commencement-speaker.html |title=UR School of Nursing Commencement Speaker Announced |last= |first= |publisher=University of Rochester |date=2017 |website=University of Rochester |access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://president.columbia.edu/berkowitz-leaving |title=Bobbie Berkowitz, Dean of the School of Nursing, to Step Down Aug. 31 |last=Bollinger |first=Lee |publisher=Columbia University |date=2018-01-25 |website=Columbia University |access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref>
Berkowitz earned her BS (1972) in [[nursing]] and her MS (1981) in nursing at [[University of Washington]], and she earned her doctorate in 1990 from [[Case Western Reserve University]].
Prior to joining [[Columbia University]] as Senior Vice President and Dean of Nursing in 2010, Berkowitz was a Professor at [[University of Washington]] and Deputy Secretary of the [[Washington State Department of Health]].
At [[Columbia University]], Berkowitz was instrumental in the creation of a new facility to house the School of Nursing,<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=2013-10-25 |title=Columbia nursing students wil get their tuition's worth from this state-of-the-art building |url=https://www.bizjournals.com/newyork/news/2013/10/24/columbia-university-nursing-school-to.html |work=New York Business Journal |access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref> that included the signature "Building the Future Gala" in honor of the 125th anniversary of the founding of the School.<ref>{{cite press release |last= |first= |date=2017-10-18 |title=Columbia Nursing “Building the Future” Gala Celebrates 125 Years of Nursing Excellence |url=https://newswise.com/articles/columbia-nursing-building-the-future-gala-celebrates-125-years-of-nursing-excellence |location=New York |publisher=Columbia University |access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref>
As part of her efforts to strengthen [[healthcare systems]], Berkowitz spoke against recommendations by the [[American Academy of Family Physicians]] and advocated for the role of the [[advanced practice registered nurse]] sharing, "There's a lot of research that [[nurse practitioners]] provide as good care if not better care than [[physicians]] in some cases."<ref>{{cite news |last=Pittman |first=David |date=2012-09-19 |title=Independent NPs Must Go, AAFP Says |url=https://www.medpagetoday.com/nursing/nursing/34843 |work=MEDPAGE Today |access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref> And in 2016, [[Columbia University]] opened a [[nurse practitioner]] [[primary care]] facility in [[Washington Heights, Manhattan]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Krisel |first=Brendan |date=2016-09-16 |title=Columbia Opens Nurse-led Medical Facility in Washington Heights |url=https://patch.com/new-york/washington-heights-inwood/columbia-opens-nurse-led-medical-facility-washington-heights |work=Washington Heights Patch |access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref>
In 2001, Berkowitz was inducted into the [[National Academy of Medicine]]. From 2014-2016, Berkowitz served as President of the [[American Academy of Nursing]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nursing.columbia.edu/dean-columbia-nursing-named-president-elect-american-academy-nursing |title=Dean of Columbia Nursing Named President-Elect of The American Academy of Nursing |last= |first= |publisher=Columbia University |date=2012 |website=Columbia University |access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref>
