The '''Collaboration for AIDS Vaccine Discovery''' ('''CAVD''') is an international network of scientists, research organizations, and promoters of [[HIV vaccine]] research.
==Partners== The CAVD was founded in 2006 when the [[Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation]] donated $287 million USD to promote HIV vaccine research.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.dukehealth.org/health_library/news/9803 |title=Gates Foundation Funds Major New Collaboration to Accelerate HIV Vaccine Development - DukeHealth.org |first= |last= |work=dukehealth.org |year=19 July 2006|accessdate=3 January 2012}}</ref> The CAVD itself supports the [[Global HIV Vaccine Enterprise]]. The network comprises many individual institutions.<ref>https://www.cavd.org/about/Pages/CollaboratingInstitutions_alpha.aspx</ref>
