The '''Tana-Beles [[Interbasin transfer|interbasin water transfer]]''' takes water from [[Lake Tana]] and delivers it to the [[Beles River]] via the [[Beles Hydroelectric Power Plant|Tana Beles hydroelectric power plant]]. The water downstream is also used for irrigation. <ref>{{cite journal |last1=Goor |first1=Q. |last2=Halleux |first2=C. |last3=Mohamed |first3=Y. |last4=Tilmant |first4=A. |title=Optimal operation of a multipurpose multireservoir system in the Eastern Nile River Basin |journal=Hydrology and Earth System Sciences |date=12 October 2010 |volume=14 |issue=10 |pages=1895–1908 |doi=10.5194/hess-14-1895-2010}}</ref>.
It was constructed between 2005 and 2010, specifically as a multi-purpose project, but with a major part of construction involving the hydropower plant, 11.8 km headrace tunnel from Lake Tana, and 7.2km tailrace tunnel to the Jehana river (minor tributary of the Beles River) <ref>{{cite web |title=Beles Multipurpose Project - Salini Impregilo |url=https://www.salini-impregilo.com/en/projects/completed/dams-hydroelectric-plants/beles-multipurpose-project.html |website=www.salini-impregilo.com |language=en}}</ref>.
While Lake Tana and the Beles River are both in the [[Blue Nile]]/Abbay basin, water would not usually flow from the lake through this river. The interbasin transfer project therefore provides substantial additional water within the Beles River region (on average 77 m<sup>3</sup>/s <ref>{{cite web |last1=Belete |first1=Mulugeta Azeze |title=Modeling and Analysis of Lake Tana Sub Basin Water Resources Systems, Ethiopia |url=http://rosdok.uni-rostock.de/file/rosdok_disshab_0000001204/rosdok_derivate_0000014925/Dissertation_Belete_2014.pdf |accessdate=9 October 2018 |date=2013}}</ref>), enabling irrigation development, notably of sugarcane <ref>{{cite book |last1=Kassahun |first1=Berhanu |last2=Tegegne |first2=Gebre-Egziabher |title=Socio-Economic Base-Line Survey of Rural and Urban Households in Tana Sub-Basin, Amhara National Regional State |date=2015 |publisher=Forum for Social Studies |isbn=9789994450497 |page=2 |url=https://books.google.fi/books?id=s9qVBgAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PP1#v=onepage&q&f=false |language=en}}</ref>.
